  "risk_regime": {
    "stance": "risk_on",
    "conviction": 76,
    "rationale": "Strong house consensus toward risk_on: 7 of 10 members are explicitly risk_on (Yahya 82, Dixon 88, Matsuoka 82, Lazzarin 75, Wuollet 82, Rosenthal 85, Jennings 75), driven by adoption all-time-highs, sub-penny fees, and a sharply improved US regulatory posture by Q1 2025. CRITICAL QUALIFIER: this is a STRUCTURAL, builder-oriented risk appetite ('long deep infrastructure, short the casino'), NOT speculative euphoria \u2014 every risk-on member is simultaneously bearish on memecoins/speculation/insider liquidity. Two members do not support a market read: Thaler is risk_off (80) purely on zk tech-maturity (not prices), and Roughgarden expresses no_view (theorist). Conviction held at 76 (not higher) because the dissenters are non-trivial and the posture is explicitly quality-filtered rather than broadly long.",
    "provenance": "grounded"
  },
  "notes": "Methodology: each item scored by coverage \u00d7 conviction, with split views (high stance_dispersion) pulled toward neutral. CONSENSUS BACKBONE (high coverage, unanimous, low dispersion): bullish zk / ai-crypto / stablecoins / l2-scaling; bearish speculation-mispricing / memecoins. These six are the firm's true shared view. NEUTRAL / NO CONSENSUS (held but split, dispersion 1.0, mean_stance_sign 0): crypto-policy-regulation \u2014 members diverge because most reversed from bearish-on-SEC to bullish-on-clarity over 2024-25, netting to neutral but trending positive; proof-of-personhood (Lazzarin bullish on World ID vs. Kominers framing it as a threat); tee-enclaves (Wuollet bullish vs. Jennings warning of trusted-vs-trustless conflation); dao-legal-entities (Jennings bullish on DUNA wrapper vs. bearish on the CA partnership-liability ruling \u2014 same member, two sides). FADED OUT (genuine high conviction but lone-member, coverage_frac 0.1, so excluded from headline lists per the weighting rule): decentralization (Jennings 98), sumcheck-snarks/zkvm/memory-checking (Thaler 90-96), nft-brands-community (Kominers 93), network-tokens & token-value-accrual (Jennings/Lazzarin 90), web3-platform-competition (Kominers 88), decentralized-energy (Wuollet 86), permissionless-consensus-hardness (Roughgarden 90). Several are specialist research/legal theses, not whole-desk market views. Lower-coverage tokens (IP, MERIT, UNI, RAI, NEAR, HNT, BASE, ZEC, LUNA) similarly faded. STRUCTURAL CAVEAT: roughly half the desk (Roughgarden, Thaler, Jennings, Wuollet, Rosenthal, Kominers) are researchers/policy/accelerator leads who rarely make tradeable token calls, so token-level convictions are systematically thinner and softer than the sector views \u2014 the real signal lives at the sector/infrastructure layer. A clear cross-desk TEMPORAL SHIFT: US-regulatory pessimism (2023-24) resolved into optimism by Q1 2025, which is why regulation-by-enforcement is down-weighted and risk appetite rose."
